#: ../../L/loss.rst:5
msgid "loss"
msgstr "loss"

#: ../../L/loss.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../L/loss.rst:9
msgid ""
"Something (not a person) that loses; a situation in which something is "
"losing. Emphatic forms include moby loss, and total loss, complete loss. "
"Common interjections are \"What a loss!\" and \"What a moby loss!\" Note "
"that moby loss is OK even though \\*\\*moby loser is not used; applied to an"
" abstract noun, moby is simply a magnifier, whereas when applied to a person"
" it implies substance and has positive connotations. Compare "
":ref:`lossage`\\."
msgstr ""
"loseする(人ではない)もの。何かがlosingしている状況。強調形にはmoby loss、そしてtotal loss、complete "
"lossがある。よくある間投詞は「What a loss!」と「What a moby loss!」である。\\*\\*\\ moby "
"loserは使われないのに、moby "
"lossは問題ないことに注意。抽象名詞に適用される場合、mobyは単なる強調語だが、人に適用される場合は実体を暗示し、肯定的な含みを持つ。\\ "
":ref:`lossage`\\ と比較せよ。"
